commit.message:
Fix loop_stop() not clearing ._thread when called from same thread

When loop_stop is called from within on_message(), ._thread will not be set to None. This will cause subsequent loop_start() to return an error.

verification.payload:
tree 044d279c37da19139156bce9b8f74a7d64e2e05f
parent 47ab9b94d9d1408abd8717e6c2d052ca329d549b
author jiachin1995 <jiachin1995@gmail.com> 1706848337 +0800
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1706848337 +0800

Fix loop_stop() not clearing ._thread when called from same thread

When loop_stop is called from within on_message(), ._thread will not be set to None. This will cause subsequent loop_start() to return an error.
